# Joseph Chee Chang | Semantic Scholar

[

## Revolt: Collaborative Crowdsourcing for Labeling Machine Learning Datasets

](/paper/Revolt%3A-Collaborative-Crowdsourcing-for-Labeling-Chang-Amershi/05f39431776d2b8858132b2118b68a6a68bf4f14)

[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[Saleema Amershi](/author/Saleema-Amershi/1719124)[Ece Kamar](/author/Ece-Kamar/1783184)

Computer Science

-   2 May 2017

Revolt eliminates the burden of creating detailed label guidelines by harnessing crowd disagreements to identify ambiguous concepts and create rich structures (groups of semantically related items) for post-hoc label decisions.

[

## SOLVENT

](/paper/SOLVENT-Chan-Chang/88b33ed41881e88ce4f38180b28b2cd85629c98a)

[Joel Chan](/author/Joel-Chan/34753665)[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[Tom Hope](/author/Tom-Hope/2041698667)[Dafna Shahaf](/author/Dafna-Shahaf/1805894)[A. Kittur](/author/A.-Kittur/145234497)

Computer Science

Proc. ACM Hum. Comput. Interact.

-   1 November 2018

SOLVENT is introduced, a mixed-initiative system where humans annotate aspects of research papers that denote their background, purpose, mechanism, and findings, and a computational model constructs a semantic representation from these annotations that can be used to find analogies among the research papers.

[

## Evorus: A Crowd-powered Conversational Assistant Built to Automate Itself Over Time

](/paper/Evorus%3A-A-Crowd-powered-Conversational-Assistant-to-Huang-Chang/9849cc224b40b7753a7721eebd02f211640f9fae)

[Ting-Hao 'Kenneth' Huang](/author/Ting-Hao-'Kenneth'-Huang/144188081)[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[Jeffrey P. Bigham](/author/Jeffrey-P.-Bigham/1744846)

Computer Science

-   8 January 2018

Evolent, a crowd-powered conversational assistant built to automate itself over time by allowing new chatbots to be easily integrated to automate more scenarios, and reusing prior crowd answers, and learning to automatically approve response candidates is introduced.

[

## SearchLens: composing and capturing complex user interests for exploratory search

](/paper/SearchLens%3A-composing-and-capturing-complex-user-Chang-Hahn/442f559bd7b7992ebf63af04f9445ae8bade12f9)

[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[Nathan Hahn](/author/Nathan-Hahn/150245582)[Adam Perer](/author/Adam-Perer/2912842)[A. Kittur](/author/A.-Kittur/145234497)

Computer Science

-   17 March 2019

Results from a controlled lab study suggest that the approach incentivized participants to express their interests more richly than in a baseline condition, and a field study showed that participants found benefits in SearchLens while conducting their own tasks.

[

## The Knowledge Accelerator: Big Picture Thinking in Small Pieces

](/paper/The-Knowledge-Accelerator%3A-Big-Picture-Thinking-in-Hahn-Chang/2a7e74ba9930a511bbc05e5c330e2e6bf1612ee6)

[Nathan Hahn](/author/Nathan-Hahn/150245582)[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[Ji Eun Kim](/author/Ji-Eun-Kim/2110811155)[A. Kittur](/author/A.-Kittur/145234497)

Computer Science

-   7 May 2016

This paper instantiates the idea that a computational system can scaffold an emerging interdependent, big picture view entirely through the small contributions of individuals through a prototype system for accomplishing distributed information synthesis and evaluates its output across a variety of topics.

[

## Alloy: Clustering with Crowds and Computation

](/paper/Alloy%3A-Clustering-with-Crowds-and-Computation-Chang-Kittur/47e3f3e976797d54951d21e7ccc185f46f82f10b)

[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[A. Kittur](/author/A.-Kittur/145234497)[Nathan Hahn](/author/Nathan-Hahn/150245582)

Computer Science

-   7 May 2016

Alloy, a hybrid approach that combines the richness of human judgments with the power of machine algorithms, is introduced, a modular "cast and gather" approach which leverages a machine learning backbone to stitch together different types of judgment tasks.

[

## Synergi: A Mixed-Initiative System for Scholarly Synthesis and Sensemaking

](/paper/Synergi%3A-A-Mixed-Initiative-System-for-Scholarly-Kang-Wu/3dbe30e02fc3547a87754361bde971d10a6dd3d5)

[Hyeonsu B Kang](/author/Hyeonsu-B-Kang/26997666)[Sherry Wu](/author/Sherry-Wu/2214836308)[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[A. Kittur](/author/A.-Kittur/145234497)

Computer Science

-   15 August 2023

A novel computational pipeline is developed that ties together user input of relevant seed threads with citation graphs and LLMs, to expand and structure them, respectively, and is found to help scholars efficiently make sense of relevant threads, broaden their perspectives, and increases their curiosity.

[

## When the Tab Comes Due:Challenges in the Cost Structure of Browser Tab Usage

](/paper/When-the-Tab-Comes-Due%3AChallenges-in-the-Cost-of-Chang-Hahn/d759863ddee9125b6ae197b053a13211241b75d1)

[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[Nathan Hahn](/author/Nathan-Hahn/150245582) [A. Kittur](/author/A.-Kittur/145234497)

Computer Science

-   6 May 2021

How tabs today are overloaded with a diverse set of functionalities and issues users face when managing them is investigated and design implications for future browser interfaces that can better support managing these pressures are developed.

[

## Bento Browser: Complex Mobile Search Without Tabs

](/paper/Bento-Browser%3A-Complex-Mobile-Search-Without-Tabs-Hahn-Chang/110604a5c936abda4f086a6ff5c58610836eb936)

[Nathan Hahn](/author/Nathan-Hahn/150245582)[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[A. Kittur](/author/A.-Kittur/145234497)

Computer Science

-   21 April 2018

This work introduces a new way of browsing through a scaffolded interface in the Bento mobile search system, finding converging evidence that users were able to make progress on their complex searching tasks with this structure, and find it more organized and easier to revisit.

[

## Recurrent-Neural-Network for Language Detection on Twitter Code-Switching Corpus

](/paper/Recurrent-Neural-Network-for-Language-Detection-on-Chang-Lin/90401aab469dbf2094d892713086c6bb9c3875f6)

[Joseph Chee Chang](/author/Joseph-Chee-Chang/48808806)[Chu-Cheng Lin](/author/Chu-Cheng-Lin/7528635)

Computer Science, Linguistics

-   13 December 2014

This paper trains recurrent neural networks with only raw features, and uses word embedding to automatically learn meaningful representations, and is able to outperform the best SVM-based systems reported in the EMNLP'14 Code-Switching Workshop by 1% in accuracy, or by 17% in error rate reduction.

Joseph Chee Chang
he/him

I am a research scientist at AI2. Previously, I obtained a PhD degree from the Language Technologies Institute at CMU specializing in Human-Computer Interaction, Sensemaking, Crowdsourcing, and Applied Machine Learning. My research focus on developing information systems to support users and crowdworkers to explore and make sense of large amounts of information and make better decisions.
